E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20267px)%2085vw%2C%20267px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F23161125%2FTerminal-column-logo.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22267%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F23161125%2FTerminal-column-logo.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F23161125%2FTerminal-column-logo-300x209.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-637305%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22187%5C%22%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20be%20real%20about%20the%20upcoming%20Bill.%20It%20is%2C%20first%20and%20foremost%2C%20inadequate%20to%20address%20the%20threats%20posed%20in%20this%20era%20of%20surveillance%20capitalism.%20The%20Bill%20is%20more%20of%20a%20rubber%20stamp%20that%20is%20coming%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20digitisation%20process%20which%20has%20been%20allowed%20to%20run%20uninterrupted%20with%20no%20safeguards%20at%20any%20stage.%20We%20needed%20a%20privacy%20law%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20but%20it%20was%20never%20a%20priority%20and%20now%20that%20we%20have%20a%20law%2C%20it%20will%20be%20one%20that%20threatens%20to%20undermine%20our%20constitutional%20rights.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20very%20idea%20of%20Digital%20India%20has%20been%20to%20promote%20a%20data%20economy%20where%20data%20is%20the%20foundation%20for%20all%20forms%20of%20economic%20transactions%20%E2%80%93%20a%20prime%20feature%20of%20surveillance%20capitalism.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20economic%20setup%2C%20by%20design%2C%20wants%20proliferation%20of%20our%20personal%20data%20through%20institutions%20that%20are%20controlled%20by%20the%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Every%20digital%20infrastructure%20project%20from%20Aadhaar%2C%20UPI%20and%20Digital%20Locker%20to%20CoWIN%20and%20Aarogya%20Setu%20has%20promoted%20this%20proliferation%20by%20providing%20Application%20Programming%20Interfaces%20to%20the%20private%20sector%20for%20building%20a%20data%20economy.%20It%20is%20this%20proliferation%20that%20is%20causing%20all%20the%20problems%20as%20it%20has%20no%20controls%20in%20place%20as%20to%20who%20uses%20our%20personal%20data.%20No%20law%20can%20change%20this%20when%20the%20systems%20remain%20the%20same.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fcowin-fiasco-should-alert-us-to-hidden-agendas-behind-digital-identity-based-governance%5C%22%3ECoWin%20Fiasco%20Should%20Alert%20Us%20to%20Hidden%20Agendas%20Behind%20Digital%20Identity-Based%20Governance%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20key%20wins%20around%20the%20public%20movement%20around%20digital%20rights%20in%20India%20has%20been%20to%20make%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20understand%20unrestricted%20proliferation%20of%20personal%20data.%20This%20is%20reflected%20in%20the%20judgement%20on%20Aadhaar%2C%20where%20the%20court%20categorically%20restricted%20and%20cut%20down%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Aadhaar%20Act%20allowing%20private%20sectors%E2%80%99%20access%20to%20Aadhaar.%20These%20wins%2C%20however%2C%20have%20been%20quickly%20over-ruled%20by%20the%20parliament%20with%20amendments%20to%20the%20Aadhaar%20Act%20to%20allow%20Aadhaar%20to%20be%20shared%20again%20with%20the%20private%20sector%20with%20the%20excuse%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20and%20good%20governance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20be%20blunt%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgements%20around%20Aadhaar%20did%20not%20result%20in%20active%20changes%20in%20the%20architecture%20or%20code%20of%20the%20Aadhaar%20system.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20I%20can%20categorically%20say%20there%20has%20not%20been%20a%20single%20line%20of%20change%20in%20the%20code%20or%20architecture%20of%20Digital%20India%20either%20because%20of%20the%20court%20judgements.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20before%20the%20judgement%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20public%20scrutiny%20of%20the%20system.%20New%20privacy-respecting%20provisions%20like%20Virtual%20ID%2C%20Masked%20Aadhaar%20and%20locking%20of%20biometrics%20were%20all%20brought%20in%20because%20of%20the%20public%20demand%20for%20privacy%20and%20security%20measures.%20While%20some%20features%20remained%20and%20some%20were%20ignored%20like%20the%20Virtual%20ID%2C%20the%20changes%20only%20happened%20because%20of%20pressure%20from%20citizenry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20cyberspace%2C%20software%20code%20becomes%20rules%20and%20architecture%20translates%20into%20legislation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdata-protection-bill-arbitrary-provisions-right-to-privacy%5C%22%3EData%20Protection%20Bill%20Is%20Riddled%20With%20Arbitrary%20Provisions%20That%20Violate%20the%20Right%20to%20Privacy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20way%20digital%20infrastructures%20are%20designed%2C%20implemented%20and%20function%20is%20entirely%20dependent%20on%20software%20code.%20In%20Digital%20India%2C%20software%20code%20enforces%20rules%20of%20government%2C%20private%20corporations%20and%20technocrats.%20These%20have%20been%20codified%20and%20turned%20invisible%20to%20society%20at%20large.%20No%20matter%20what%20a%20judgement%20of%20a%20court%2C%20a%20legislation%20by%20the%20legislature%20or%20a%20rule%20by%20the%20government%20is%2C%20as%20long%20as%20the%20code%20remains%20unchanged%2C%20these%20laws%20of%20humans%20are%20not%20being%20enforced%20by%20machines.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhatever%20form%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20may%20take%2C%20good%2C%20bad%20or%20ugly%2C%20it%20will%20not%20help%20if%20the%20engineers%20who%20build%20these%20systems%20do%20not%20change%20their%20software%20to%20adapt%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20law.%20Even%20with%20a%20very%20good%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20with%20an%20independent%20regulator%20which%20really%20wants%20to%20implement%20the%20law%2C%20it%20will%20be%20really%20hard%20to%20change%20decades%20of%20digitisation%20that%20led%20to%20so%20many%20social%20problems.%20Enforceability%20of%20laws%20has%20never%20been%20a%20strong%20domain%20of%20the%20Indian%20state%2C%20and%20especially%20with%20cyberspace%2C%20it%20becomes%20a%20challenge%20in%20many%20different%20ways.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGiven%20this%20background%2C%20members%20of%20legislature%20and%20the%20judiciary%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20oblivious%20around%20this%20issue%20while%20designing%20social%20protections%20for%20the%20public.%20If%20the%20laws%20of%20the%20land%20are%20being%20made%20so%20distant%20from%20social%20realities%2C%20then%20the%20process%20in%20itself%20is%20devoid%20of%20legitimacy.%20This%20is%20especially%20true%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%20where%20at%20every%20stage%20economic%20interests%20were%20used%20as%20an%20excuse%20to%20limit%20discourse%20and%20need%20for%20social%20protections.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Findia-data-protection-authority-needs-constitutional-entrenchment%5C%22%3EWhy%20India%E2%80%99s%20Proposed%20Data%20Protection%20Authority%20Needs%20Constitutional%20Entrenchment%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20digital%20economy%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20social%20need%20where%20certain%20practices%20that%20may%20promote%20digitisation%2C%20are%20also%20harming%20society%20at%20large.%20It%20is%20these%20social%20harms%20that%20need%20to%20be%20arrested%2C%20while%20allowing%20safe%20practices%20to%20flourish.%20The%20current%20version%20of%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20will%20not%20do%20that.%20As%20much%20as%20one%20wants%20a%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20to%20be%20quickly%20enacted%2C%20these%20poorly%20drafted%20laws%2C%20which%20do%20not%20protect%20the%20citizenry%2C%20are%20of%20no%20use%20other%20than%20to%20make%20media%20announcements%20that%20claim%20that%20we%20are%20the%20best%20digital%20society%20in%20the%20world.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202022%2C%20will%20do%20more%20harm%20to%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20privacy%20than%20help%20protect%20it%20%E2%80%93%20with%20all%20the%20exceptions%20it%20provides.%20With%20this%20version%20of%20the%20bill%2C%20the%20state%20is%20making%20its%20intent%20clear%20that%20it%20has%20no%20interest%20in%20safeguarding%20our%20fundamental%20rights.%20In%20such%20a%20situation%2C%20it%20is%20up%20to%20people%20to%20educate%20themselves%20and%20stay%20safe%20as%20the%20guard%20has%20now%20turned%20into%20a%20thief%20himself.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESrinivas%20Kodali%20is%20a%20researcher%20on%20digitisation%20and%20hacktivist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1688985092000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F06095248%2FUntitled-design-4.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fdata-protection-bull-proliferation-digital-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20the%20laws%20of%20the%20land%20are%20being%20made%20so%20distant%20from%20social%20realities%2C%20then%20the%20process%20in%20itself%20is%20devoid%20of%20legitimacy.%22%2C%22topic%22%3A%22https%3A%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fdata-protection-bull-proliferation-digital-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'We're%20all%20going%20to%20die'%3A%20Chesney%20Hawkes%20recalls%20'terrifying%20ordeal'%20as%20plane%20plunged%2020%2C000ft%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22publis