C%20which%20he%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20first%20really%20interesting%20thing%20I%20worked%20on.%26quot%3B%20He%20was%20happy%20to%20feel%20like%20a%20valuable%20member%20of%20the%20team%2C%20but%20Graham's%20manager%20told%20him%20something%20stunning%3A%20The%20finished%20project%2C%20which%20Graham%20worked%20on%20for%20more%20than%20a%20month%2C%20wouldn't%20see%20the%20light%20of%20day.%20It%20was%20simply%20an%20exercise%20to%20satisfy%20the%20terms%20of%20his%20performance%20plan%20and%20string%20out%20his%20employment%2C%20he%20was%20told.%20Graham%20left%20Amazon%20soon%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20tech%20companies%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-sweeping-the-us-these-are-the-companies-making-cuts-2023%5C%22%3Elaid%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20employees%20this%20year%2C%20venture%20capitalists%20and%20executives%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-debates-tech-employees-doing-fake-work-2023-3%5C%22%3Eleaned%20on%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bfake%20work%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20describe%20the%20output%20of%20employees%20like%20Graham.%20The%20layoffs%20are%20necessary%20and%20even%20prudent%2C%20the%20argument%20goes%2C%20because%20thousands%20of%20workers%20at%20Big%20Tech%20firms%20such%20as%20Google%20and%20Meta%20are%20sitting%20around%20trying%20to%20look%20busy%20while%20doing%20very%20little%20productive%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20nothing%20for%20these%20people%20to%20do%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20all%20fake%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Keith%20Rabois%2C%20a%20famous%20tech%20investor%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-meta-staff-do-fake-work-says-vc-keith-rabois-2023-3%5C%22%3Eopined%20at%20a%20March%20event%3C%2Fa%3E%20hosted%20by%20the%20investment%20bank%20Evercore.%20%26quot%3BNow%20that's%20being%20exposed%2C%20what%20do%20these%20people%20actually%20do%3F%20They%20go%20to%20meetings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20tech%20workers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffired-from-my-job-at-meta-for-posting-on-tiktok-2023-3%5C%22%3Eseemed%20to%20confirm%3C%2Fa%3E%20Rabois'%20claims%20on%20social%20media%2C%20sharing%20stories%20of%20being%20paid%20by%20giant%20tech%20firms%20to%20do%20very%20little.%20In%20one%20viral%20TikTok%20video%2C%20Brit%20Levy%2C%20Meta's%20former%20diversity%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20inclusion%20policy%20analyst%2C%20said%20she%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-meta-employee-says-paid-not-to-work-2023-3%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bbasically%20fight%20to%20find%20work%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20company%20was%20simply%20holding%20on%20to%20employees%20%26quot%3Blike%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20cards.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20based%20on%20conversations%20with%20over%2030%20people%20involved%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20including%20current%20and%20former%20tech%20employees%2C%20some%20in%20management%20positions%2C%20the%20conception%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-debates-tech-employees-doing-fake-work-2023-3%5C%22%3Elazy%20employees%20raking%20in%20big%20paychecks%20to%20do%20little%3C%2Fa%3E%20lays%20the%20blame%20in%20the%20wrong%20place.%20Oftentimes%2C%20employees%20are%20getting%20plenty%20of%20work%20done%3B%20it's%20just%20that%20the%20projects%20are%20of%20little%20to%20no%20importance%20to%20the%20company's%20bottom%20line.%20The%20tech%20employees%20spoke%20with%20us%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20to%20avoid%20professional%20reprisal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20workers%20want%20to%20come%20and%20work.%20They%20want%20to%20show%20up%2C%20give%20a%20fair%20eight%20hours%20of%20work%2C%20and%20they%20want%20to%20feel%20good%20about%20themselves%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Scott%20Latham%2C%20a%20strategic-management%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Massachusetts%20Lowell%20who%20worked%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%20during%20the%20start%20of%20the%20internet%20boom.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20only%20one%20real%20culprit%20for%20the%20culture%20of%20%26quot%3Bfake%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20lazy%20management.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20we%20talk%20about%20when%20we%20talk%20about%20'fake%20work'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFake%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20consultants%20Brent%20Peterson%20and%20Gaylan%20Nielson%20define%20it%20in%20their%202009%20book%20of%20the%20same%20name%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Beffort%20under%20the%20illusion%20of%20value.%26quot%3B%20The%20crimes%2C%20they%20wrote%2C%20include%20pointless%20meetings%2C%20reports%2C%20and%20presentations.%20In%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20specifically%2C%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bfake%20work%26quot%3B%20is%20used%20to%20conjure%20up%20an%20image%20of%20lazy%20engineers%20%26quot%3Bresting%20and%20vesting%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20long-tenured%2C%20high-paid%20employees%20doing%20very%20little%20work%20while%20waiting%20on%20a%20lucrative%20payday%20from%20their%20company%20stock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERich%20Moran%2C%20a%20venture%20capitalist%2C%20consultant%2C%20and%20author%20of%20several%20books%20about%20the%20workplace%2C%20prefers%20to%20call%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bfalse%20sense%20of%20activity%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20it's%20%26quot%3Bmore%20rampant%26quot%3B%20among%20tech%20companies.%20%26quot%3BThe%20tech%20sector%20is%20more%20willing%20to%20try%20different%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20us.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20you%20get%20assigned%20to%20a%20project%20that%20you%20know%20may%20be%20going%20nowhere%2C%20but%20they%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20saying%2C%20well%20this%20isn't%20going%20anywhere.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20version%20of%20fake%20work%20emerged%20as%20part%20of%20the%20tech%20industry's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-moonshots-over-amazon-facebook-google-microsoft-2022-9%5C%22%3Epandemic-driven%20boom%20and%20bust%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Lockdowns%20and%20work%20from%20home%20meant%20Amazon%2C%20Google%2C%20Meta%2C%20Shopify%2C%20and%20many%20other%20giants%20saw%20an%20explosion%20of%20demand%20for%20their%20products.%20Assuming%20the%20consumer%20shift%20was%20a%20harbinger%20of%20a%20new%20normal%20of%20shopping%2C%20socializing%2C%20and%20working%20online%20all%20the%20time%2C%20companies%20aggressively%20hired%20thousands%20of%20recruits.%20But%20firms%20often%20gave%20little%20thought%20about%20where%20to%20place%20them%20or%20what%20their%20role%20would%20be%2C%20insiders%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20COVID%20was%20an%20accelerator%20for%20fake%20work%20because%20a%20lot%20of%20these%20tech%20companies%20hired.%20Then%20they%20weren't%20sure%20what%20to%20do%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Moran%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20former%20Google%20manager%20told%20us%20she%20was%20instructed%20to%20lower%20her%20standards%20for%20hiring%20earlier%20in%20the%20pandemic%20and%20watched%20as%20teams%20she%20worked%20with%20doubled%20in%20size.%20As%20new%20hires%20flooded%20in%2C%20it%20felt%20as%20if%20teams%20were%20reorganized%20on%20a%20weekly%20basis%2C%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20people%20to%20do%20solid%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EMost%20workers%20want%20to%20come%20and%20work.%20They%20want%20to%20show%20up%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sudden%20head-count%20increase%20was%20destabilizing%2C%20but%20the%20real%20trouble%20began%20when%20business%20started%20to%20slow%20down.%20Rather%20than%20a%20permanent%20reorientation%2C%20many%20of%20the%20behaviors%20people%20adopted%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20short-term%20modifications.%20And%20as%20the%20economy%20turned%20on%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20companies%20scrambled%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20to%20do%20with%20all%20the%20employees%20they%20no%20longer%20needed.%20That's%20when%20the%20%26quot%3Bfake%20work%26quot%3B%20talk%2C%20finger-pointing%2C%20and%20unceremonious%20layoffs%20took%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20just%20no%20guidance%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20ex-Meta%20worker%20said%20of%20his%20two%20months%20at%20the%20company%2C%20when%20he%20was%20waiting%20to%20be%20placed%20on%20a%20team%20as%20an%20entry-level%20data%20scientist.%20%26quot%3BI%20remember%20one%20day%20literally%20having%20absolutely%20nothing%20to%20do%2C%20and%20I%20just%20went%20surfing%20instead%20because%20I'm%20remote.%20I%20have%20no%20one%20to%20report%20to.%20It%20seems%20like%20no%20one%20knows%20I'm%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20with%20a%20backpack%20walks%20up%20to%20a%20glass%20building%20with%20the%20Google%20logo%20on%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a84d368ed31300199e1ea8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20former%20Google%20employee%20said%20many%20employees%20were%20assigned%20work%20that%20served%20no%20purpose%20for%20the%20company.%3Cp%3EMelina%20Mara%2FThe%20Washington%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20ex-Meta%20employee%20said%20that%20there%20were%20so%20many%20workers%20in%20his%20department%20when%20he%20joined%20in%202022%20that%20on%20multiple%20occasions%2C%20he'd%20complete%20a%20project%20to%20learn%20that%20as%20many%20as%20four%20other%20people%20had%20been%20given%20the%20same%20assignment%20separately.%20The%20former%20employee%20described%20the%20work%20he%20did%20at%20Meta%20as%20%26quot%3Bintern-level'%20%E2%80%94%20putting%20together%20graphs%20based%20on%20preexisting%20data%2C%20polishing%20presentations%2C%20or%20practicing%20how%20to%20%26quot%3Bwork%20a%20problem%20backward%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20despite%20having%20nearly%20a%20decade%20of%20experience%20in%20tech.%20He%20said%20he%20found%20the%20environment%20%26quot%3Bstifling%26quot%3B%20and%20was%20often%20deterred%20from%20trying%20to%20increase%20the%20scope%20of%20his%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20there%20were%20some%20employees%2C%20as%20pundits%20and%20executives%20have%20suggested%2C%20who%20could%20have%20helped%20tackle%20projects%20but%20chose%20not%20to.%20But%20for%20the%20most%20part%2C%20insiders%20told%20us%2C%20workers%20were%20stuck%20in%20circumstances%20beyond%20their%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20there's%20very%20few%20people%20sitting%20around%20doing%20nothing%2C%26quot%3B%20Moran%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20people%20are%20very%20skilled%20at%20filling%20their%20time.%20Whether%20or%20not%20it%20helps%20the%20organization%20is%20another%20question.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20were%20assigned%20plenty%20of%20tasks%2C%20but%20they%20ended%20up%20serving%20no%20mission-critical%20purpose.%20The%20former%20Google%20program%20manager%20said%20that%20people%20were%20working%20hard%20but%20what%20qualified%20as%20work%20had%20seemingly%20changed.%20%26quot%3BThey%20gave%20us%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20that%20was%20just%20a%20waste%20of%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%2C%20like%20Graham%2C%20were%20assigned%20to%20seemingly%20key%20parts%20of%20the%20company%2C%20only%20to%20find%20that%20there%20wasn't%20enough%20work%20to%20go%20around.%20The%20former%20Googler%20also%20noticed%20this%20type%20of%20fake%20work.%20%26quot%3BThere%20were%20so%20many%20of%20us%2C%20people%20just%20started%20trying%20to%20look%20busy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20us.%20%26quot%3BThere%20were%20too%20many%20chefs%20in%20the%20kitchen%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20former%20contract%20worker%20hired%20by%20Meta%20during%20the%20pandemic%20became%20so%20frustrated%20with%20feeling%20idle%20that%20she%20took%20on%20a%20second%20contract%20job%20at%20Microsoft%20at%20the%20same%20time%20(neither%20company%20knew%20she%20was%20working%20for%20the%20other).%20She%20decided%20if%20%26quot%3Bthey're%20not%20going%20to%20give%20me%20anything%20to%20do%20then%20I%20guess%20I'm%20just%20getting%20paid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20a%20symbiotic%20relationship%20where%20the%20people%20that%20you%20report%20to%20aren't%20saying%20that%20you're%20not%20doing%20anything%20and%20you're%20not%20saying%20that%20you're%20not%20doing%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20us.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EEmpty%20empires%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20pandemic's%20boom%20and%20bust%20brought%20the%20issue%20into%20stark%20relief%2C%20the%20various%20types%20of%20fake%20work%20have%20been%20growing%20within%20tech%20companies%20for%20years.%20Many%20of%20these%20issues%20come%20down%20to%20one%20fundamental%20problem%3A%20managers%20trying%20to%20get%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20almost%20all%20tech%20companies%2C%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20said%2C%20bosses%20were%20rewarded%20for%20overhiring%20since%20it%20made%20them%20look%20important.%20Bloated%20org%20charts%20resulted%20in%20too%20many%20people%20fighting%20for%20work%2C%20a%20poor%20understanding%20of%20what%20each%20segment%20of%20the%20company%20was%20doing%2C%20and%20a%20rise%20in%20projects%20spun%20up%20merely%20to%20help%20managers%20get%20themselves%20promoted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20often%20measured%20not%20in%20contribution%20but%20in%20head%20count.%26quot%3B%20Moran%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20bigger%20your%20team%20you%20have%2C%20the%20more%20qualified%20people%20you%20have%20in%20your%20team%2C%20the%20more%20weight%20you%20have%20in%20the%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20Graham%2C%20the%20former%20Amazon%20employee%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20what%20we%20call%20empire%20building.%20You're%20not%20focused%20on%20building%20a%20product%3B%20you're%20focused%20on%20building%20an%20empire.%20That%20leads%20to%20fake%20work%20and%20unnecessary%20bloating.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThe%20more%20people%20who%20report%20to%20you%2C%20the%20higher%20your%20prestige%2C%20the%20more%20your%20power%20in%20the%20organization.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20create%20an%20empire%2C%20managers%20simply%20add%20employees%20underneath%20them%20with%20little%20sense%20of%20what%20they%20should%20be%20doing.%20%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20planning%20in%20the%20most%20efficient%20way%2C%20they%20just%20say%2C%20'I%20need%20a%20head%20count%2C'%26quot%3B%20Anna%20Tavis%2C%20a%20clinical%20professor%20of%20human-capital%20management%20at%20New%20York%20University's%20School%20of%20Professional%20Studies%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20Meta%20employee%20who%20joined%20the%20company%20in%202022%20felt%20that%20stuffing%20teams%20was%20a%20byproduct%20of%20middle%20managers%20looking%20for%20a%20promotion%2C%20leading%20to%20employees%20having%20less%20to%20do.%20One%20of%20his%20managers%20hired%20so%20many%20people%20that%20within%20three%20months%2C%20there%20became%20four%20levels%20between%20him%20and%20the%20person%20who%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20managing%20him.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20the%20time%2C%20my%20managers%20had%20no%20idea%20what%20I%20was%20doing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20incentive%20structure%20encouraging%20projects%20to%20nowhere%2C%20there's%20a%20lack%20of%20oversight%20from%20the%20top%20into%20how%20these%20miniature%20empires%20are%20being%20run%2C%20employees%20said.%20And%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20executives%20are%20oblivious%20to%20the%20value%20of%20the%20work%20that's%20presented%20to%20them.%20Some%20executives%20have%20even%20admitted%20that%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20little%20incentive%20to%20address%20company%20bloat.%20Former%20Slack%20CEO%20Stewart%20Butterfield%20told%20Bloomberg's%20%26quot%3BOdd%20Lots%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fomny.fm%2Fshows%2Fodd-lots%2Fslack-founder-stewart-butterfield-on-ai-software-a%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epodcast%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20without%20financial%20hurdles%2C%20managers%20had%20every%20reason%20to%20keep%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20people%20who%20report%20to%20you%2C%20the%20higher%20your%20prestige%2C%20the%20more%20your%20power%20in%20the%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20secure%20their%20fiefdoms%2C%20managers%20often%20pitch%20projects%20they%20created%20that%20are%20sometimes%20referred%20to%20as%20%26quot%3Bvanity%20projects%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bpromo%20projects.%26quot%3B%20These%20may%20ultimately%20contribute%20zero%20to%20a%20company's%20top%20line%2C%20but%20the%20flashy%20presentations%20and%20demos%20associated%20with%20the%20projects%20often%20lead%20to%20a%20promotion%20and%20nice%20pay%20bump%20for%20the%20person%20leading%20the%20work.%20One%20Google%20manager%20who%20recently%20left%20the%20company%20said%20the%20head-count%20process%20at%20Google%20%26quot%3Brewards%20bad%20behavior%26quot%3B%20by%20promoting%20people%20based%20on%20%26quot%3Bhaving%20a%20bigger%20team%20and%20creating%20decks.%26quot%3B%20Google%20had%20%26quot%3Bdozens%26quot%3B%20of%20teams%2C%20he%20said%2C%20that%20did%20%26quot%3Bthink%20tank-like%20strategy%20work%20with%20no%20real%20practical%20way%20of%20impacting%20the%20business%20or%20a%20customer%20or%20user.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20think%20that%20process%20favored%20the%20people%20who%20were%20better%20at%20bullshitting%20and%20storytelling%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225119%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon%20employees%20at%20the%20Spheres%20next%20to%20its%20Seattle%20headquarters%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a84df48ed31300199e1ed0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGraham%2C%20a%20former%20Amazon%20employee%2C%20said%20the%20incentive%20structure%20at%20the%20company%20led%20to%20%26quot%3Bfake%20work%20and%20unnecessary%20bloating.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ELINDSEY%20WASSON%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Meta%2C%20one%20current%20employee%20said%20it%20was%20common%20to%20see%20employees%20all%20the%20way%20up%20to%20vice%20presidents%20invent%20workshops%20or%20%26quot%3Bsprints%26quot%3B%20to%20set%20%26quot%3Bstrategic%20visions%26quot%3B%20for%20projects%2C%20while%20only%20a%20small%20fraction%20made%20it%20onto%20a%20road%20map%2C%20an%20actual%20timeline%20for%20a%20product%20to%20launch%20to%20the%20public%2C%20the%20employee%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20rarely%20seen%20a%20large-scale%20vision%20be%20referenced%20after%20it's%20presented%2C%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20upwards%20of%2020%20people%20are%20called%20to%20participate%2C%20usually%20by%20making%20and%20remaking%20decks%20for%20leadership%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20added.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20always%20tell%20when%20performance%20reviews%20are%20about%20to%20happen%20because%20there's%20almost%20always%20one%20or%20two%20workshops%20on%20the%20calendar%20a%20month%20before.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20that%20manager%20gets%20promoted%20%E2%80%94%20or%20the%20project%20falls%20apart%20%E2%80%94%20the%20team%20is%20sometimes%20shuffled%20into%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20business.%20Several%20tech%20employees%20told%20us%20these%20situations%20led%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20that%20ultimately%20made%20little%20or%20no%20material%20impact%20on%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20reorg%20after%20another%20led%20to%20fake%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20longtime%20Google%20employee%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20got%20used%20to%20getting%20introduced%20to%20a%20multiyear%20product%2C%20for%20a%20project%20I%20would%20look%20at%20and%20say%2C%20'This%20is%20a%20poster%20piece%20for%20some%20executive%20to%20implement%20while%20job%20hunting%20for%20another%20role%20so%20they%20can%20go%20be%20a%20CEO%20somewhere.'%20They%20were%20show%20products.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EI%20do%20think%20that%20process%20favored%20the%20people%20who%20were%20better%20at%20bullshitting%20and%20storytelling.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20power-jockeying%20adds%20layers%20of%20unnecessary%20complication%2C%20making%20it%20nearly%20impossible%20to%20complete%20simple%20tasks.%20One%20former%20manager%20at%20Salesforce%20said%20the%20company%20had%20in%20recent%20years%20become%20stuffed%20with%20middle%20managers%20and%20power%20structures%20that%20sucked%20up%20resources%20but%20made%20it%20hard%20to%20get%20anything%20of%20substance%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrying%20to%20get%20anything%20done%20in%20that%20organization%20takes%2040%20people%20to%20get%20aligned%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20former%20employee%20told%20us.%20He%20said%20the%20meeting%20culture%20at%20the%20company%20had%20also%20gotten%20out%20of%20hand%20and%20%26quot%3Bwork%26quot%3B%20was%20defined%20as%20%26quot%3Bmaking%20slide%20decks%20and%20giving%20speeches%20and%20having%20a%20really%20full%20calendar%20that%20shows%20you're%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20meetings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat's%20next%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20year%2C%20tech%20companies%20have%20made%20it%20very%20clear%20how%20they%20plan%20to%20deal%20with%20fake%20work%20%E2%80%94%20layoffs%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20almost%20every%20layoff%20announcement%20%E2%80%94%20those%20from%20Amazon%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20Google%2C%20Salesforce%2C%20and%20others%20%E2%80%94%20executives%20have%20focused%20on%20the%20need%20to%20get%20more%20efficient.%20After%20announcing%20the%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-employees-facebook-mark-zuckerberg-metaverse-bet-2022-11%5C%22%3Efirst%20round%20of%20job%20cuts%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%2C%20Meta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-year-efficiency-meta-facebook-could-mean-more-layoffs-2023-2%5C%22%3Edeclared%3C%2Fa%3E%202023%20would%20be%20the%20%26quot%3Byear%20of%20efficiency.%26quot%3B%20Other%20tech%20CEOs%2C%20such%20as%20Alphabet's%20Sundar%20Pichai%2C%20have%20also%20talked%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-productivity-sundar-pichai-improved-ceo-2022-8%5C%22%3Eincreasing%20their%20companies'%20productivity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20companies%20have%20also%20shown%20signs%20that%20they're%20trying%20to%20curb%20busywork.%20In%20September%2C%20Google%20told%20staff%20it%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-cut-back-meetings-distractions-okrs-goals-simplicity-sprint-2022-9%5C%22%3Ecut%20down%20%26quot%3Bredundant%20meetings%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20asked%20employees%20to%20make%20stronger%20and%20specific%20agendas%20for%20the%20meetings%20they%20did%20have.%20In%20January%2C%20Zuckerberg%20told%20staff%20that%20he%20could%20no%20longer%20tolerate%20a%20company%20structure%20of%20%26quot%3Bmanagers%20managing%20managers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20newsletter%20Command%20Line%20reported.%20He%20also%20told%20middle%20managers%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-facebook-mark-zuckerberg-layoffs-managers-asked-to-move-quit-2023-2%5C%22%3Efind%20roles%20as%20individual%20contributors%20or%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20many%20big%20tech%20companies%20have%20emphasized%20the%20need%20for%20more%20%26quot%3Befficiency%26quot%3B%20over%20the%20past%20six%20months%2C%20they%20have%20also%20generally%20downplayed%20concerns%20about%20their%20workplace%20cultures.%20In%20a%20statement%2C%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20Brad%20Glasser%20said%20that%20Graham's%20story%20%26quot%3Bdoesn't%20reflect%20the%20experience%20of%20most%20employees.%26quot%3B%20A%20Google%20spokesperson%20denied%20that%20managers%20had%20been%20told%20to%20lower%20hiring%20standards%20during%20the%20pandemic%20and%20pointed%20us%20to%20to%20an%20interview%20with%20Bloomberg%20where%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%20remarked%20that%20the%20company%20was%20%26quot%3Bsharpening%20its%20focus.%26quot%3B%20Representatives%20from%20Salesforce%2C%20and%20Microsoft%20declined%20to%20comment.%20Meta%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreg%20Selker%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20the%20executive-search%20and%20consulting%20firm%20Stanton%20Chase%2C%20said%20he%20thought%20the%20fake-work%20phenomenon%20was%20already%20reaching%20a%20natural%20conclusion.%20The%20%26quot%3Bsmartest%20companies%26quot%3B%20that%20overhired%20have%20already%20gone%20through%20significant%20bloodletting%2C%20while%20others%20will%20soon%20realize%20they%20have%20to%20do%20the%20same%2C%20he%20said%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20all%20insiders%20are%20convinced.%20Some%20said%20these%20companies%20would%20need%20to%20make%20more%20drastic%20changes%20to%20the%20culture%20if%20they%20wanted%20to%20undo%20years%20of%20%26quot%3Bfake%20work.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BThe%20dirty%20secret%20of%20these%20layoffs%20is%20that%20they're%20not%20materially%20changing%20these%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20longtime%20Google%20executive%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAddressing%20the%20issue%20of%20bloat%20and%20poor%20management%20takes%20more%20than%20a%20few%20layoffs.%20Jessica%20Kennedy%2C%20an%20organizational%20expert%20out%20of%20Vanderbilt%20University%2C%20said%20it%20came%20down%20to%20clear%20communication%20and%20proper%20incentives%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20issue%20could%20be%20solved%20with%20better%20organization%20and%20a%20clearer%2C%20more%20transparent%20differentiation%20between%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EWe%20have%20a%20good%20leader%2C%20which%20makes%20all%20the%20difference.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20natural%20for%20a%20worker%20to%20try%20and%20find%20a%20way%20to%20increase%20their%20status%20or%20differentiate%20themselves%2C%20but%20cultures%20are%20set%20by%20the%20people%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20organization%2C%20and%20it's%20their%20job%20to%20incentivize%20the%20right%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Kennedy%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20probably%20an%20issue%20a%20company%20would%20face%20if%20it%20focused%20too%20much%20on%20rewarding%20social%20status%20instead%20of%20performance.%20It's%20important%20employees%20understand%20the%20overlying%20purpose%20of%20the%20work%20they%20do.%20Good%20leaders%20know%20how%20to%20properly%20motivate%20their%20employees.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20level%20of%20redundancy%20is%20a%20good%20thing%20if%20companies%20want%20to%20%26quot%3Bbuild%20for%20resilience%20and%20innovation%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20there%20needs%20to%20be%20careful%20thought%20given%20to%20it%2C%20NYU's%20Tavis%20said.%20%26quot%3BCompanies%20making%20profits%20can%20become%20lazy%20around%20really%20planning%20for%20what%20they%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20us.%20%26quot%3BYes%2C%20you%20need%20to%20create%20resilience%20and%20innovation%2C%20but%20you%20need%20to%20plan%20for%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Graham%2C%20he's%20since%20moved%20to%20another%20tech%20company%2C%20where%20he%20said%20he%20felt%20his%20contributions%20were%20more%20valued.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20good%20work%20so%20far%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20good%20leader%2C%20which%20makes%20all%20the%20difference.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%222b64df0f6372b793adf44f92de551127%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fhugh-langley%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3EHugh%20Langley%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Insider%20covering%20Alphabet%20and%20tech%20investigations.%20He%20can%20be%20reached%20via%20encrypted%20messaging%20app%20Signal%20at%20%2B1%20628-228-1836%20and%20email%20at%20hlangley%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%