Tourists%20from%20across%20the%20world%20visit%20the%20bar%20to%20try%20the%20iconic%20drink.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22sqnbvto%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fsqnbvto_singapore-sling_625x300_09_July_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20why%20are%20tourists%20so%20obsessed%20with%20this%20drink%3F%20Well%2C%20the%20answer%20lies%20in%20its%20history.%20The%20News.com.au%20report%20said%20Raffles'%20Long%20Bar%20was%20a%20popular%20gathering%20place%20for%20the%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Raffles'%20website%2C%20etiquette%20rules%20at%20the%20time%20mandated%20that%20it%20was%20unacceptable%20for%20women%20to%20drink%20alcohol%20in%20public.%20Instead%2C%20they%20would%20often%20drink%20tea%20or%20fruit%20juice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBartender%20Ngiam%20had%20a%20light-bulb%20moment.%20He%20decided%20to%20create%20a%20cocktail%20that%20look%20like%20fruit%20juice%2C%20but%20it%20was%20infused%20with%20gin%2C%20grenadine%20and%20cherry%20liqueur.%20The%20pink%20colour%20of%20the%20cocktail%20gave%20it%20a%20'feminine%20flair'%20and%20people%20thought%20that%20it%20was%20a%20socially%20acceptable%20drink%20for%20women.%20And%20with%20that%20the%20Singapore%20Sling%20was%20born%2C%20a%20world-famous%20drink%20that%20continues%20to%20attract%20tourists%20to%20the%20bar%20more%20than%20100%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bar%20has%20another%20unique%20tradition%2C%20guests%20are%20served%20peanuts%20and%20are%20encouraged%20to%20throw%20the%20shells%20all%20over%20the%20floor.%20While%20littering%20in%20Singapore%20is%20not%20allowed%2C%20the%20hotel's%20website%20says%20that%20it%20is%20the%20only%20place%20where%20littering%20is%20'encouraged'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnypost.com%2F2023%2F07%2F09%2Fthis-hotel-makes-nearly-30k-per-day-for-just-one-drink%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20