ment%20and%20training%20cost%20for%20the%20bank%2C%20which%20becomes%20an%20investment%20if%20they%20continue%20to%20be%20in%20the%20bank%20for%20some%20years.%20But%20when%20attrition%20is%20so%20high%2C%20the%20costs%20become%20an%20expense%2C%20as%20freshers%20normally%20take%20around%209%20months%20to%20break%20even%20for%20the%20bank.%20The%20consistently%20high%20attrition%20in%20these%20categories%20indicates%20a%20combination%20of%20poor%20selection%20practices%20by%20the%20bank%E2%80%99s%20recruitment%20team%2C%20inadequate%20training%20and%20a%20stressful%20work%20culture.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20attrition%20regularly%20exceeds%2030-40%25%20in%20these%20categories%2C%20the%20bank%20has%20a%20major%20human%20resource%20management%20issue%20which%20the%20board%20of%20directors%20has%20failed%20to%20address.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20attrition%20getting%20worse%20in%20Axis%20Bank%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20data%20which%20the%20bank%20earlier%20voluntarily%20disclosed%20is%20worrying.%20But%20further%2C%20there%20is%20also%20a%20lack%20of%20in-depth%20management%20discussion%20on%20attrition.%20The%20only%20significant%20reference%20to%20attrition%20is%20the%20following%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20an%20effort%20to%20control%20attrition%20at%20various%20levels%2C%20the%20Bank%20introduced%20a%20KRA%20%5BKey%20Result%2FResponsibility%20Areas%5D%20focused%20on%20team%20retention%20for%20all%20AVP%20%5BAssistant%20Vice-President%5D%20and%20above%20team%20leaders%20with%20a%20team%20size%20of%20more%20than%204.%20So%20far%2C%20the%20same%20has%20been%20implemented%20across%20more%20than%2090%25%20leaders.%E2%80%9D%20(p.%20134%20Axis%20Bank%20FY2023%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axisbank.com%2Fdocs%2Fdefault-source%2Fannual-reports%2Ffor-axis-bank%2Fannual-report-for-the-year-2022-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAnnual%20Report%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStakeholders%20are%20also%20informed%20that%20one%20of%20the%20seven%20observations%20and%20actions%20taken%20by%20the%20board%20of%20the%20bank%E2%80%99s%20performance%20evaluation%20for%20FY2022%20was%20%E2%80%9Coversight%20on%20actionables%20relating%20to%20attrition%20and%20customer%20complaints.%E2%80%9D%20(p.%20156%20Axis%20Bank%20FY2023%20Annual%20Report)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20heartening%20to%20know%20that%20this%20mass%20exodus%20has%20not%20entirely%20escaped%20the%20board%E2%80%99s%20notice.%20However%2C%20these%20statements%20do%20not%20tell%20us%20anything%20about%20the%20causes%20of%20attrition.%20They%20do%20not%20acknowledge%20the%20fact%20that%20attrition%20has%20been%20rising%20in%20the%20last%203%20years%2C%20or%20that%20more%20than%20a%20third%20of%20the%20workforce%20jumped%20ship%20in%20the%20year.%20The%20board%E2%80%99s%20remedial%20measures%C2%A0%20also%20do%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20working%3A%20attrition%20actually%20rose%20during%20the%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAxis%20Bank%20stakeholders%20are%20in%20the%20dark%20on%20attrition%3B%20is%20it%20rising%20because%20it%20is%20an%20industry%20phenomenon%2C%20or%20is%20there%20something%20unique%20to%20Axis%20Bank%20such%20as%20poor%20selection%20for%20roles%2C%20inadequate%20resources%20to%20meet%20over%20ambitious%20sales%20targets%2C%20long%20working%20hours%2C%20low%20remunerations%2C%20inappropriate%20training%20despite%20the%20bank%20on%20average%20providing%2087%20hours%20per%20employee%20and%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhemindrahazari.com%2F2022%2F01%2F10%2Faxis-banks-toxic-call-to-staff-to-fight-abuse-and-undermine-one-another-in-pursuit-of-business%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etoxic%20work%20culture%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EConsequently%2C%20what%20additional%20steps%20is%20the%20board%20of%20directors%20taking%20to%20address%20this%20important%20issue%3F%20Recall%20that%20M.K.%20Jain%2C%20the%20then%20deputy%20governor%20of%20the%20RBI%20addressed%20the%20boards%20of%20directors%20of%20banks%20on%20May%2031%2C%202023%2C%20pointedly%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rbi.org.in%2FScripts%2FBS_SpeechesView.aspx%3FId%3D1365%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estating%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20there%20is%20operational%20risk%20due%20to%20various%20factors%20such%20as%20high%20attrition%2C%20lack%20of%20succession%20planning%2C%20skilling%20of%20staff%2C%20outsourcing%2C%20etc.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EAttrition%20and%20high%20employee%20turnover%20lead%20to%20loss%20of%20institutional%20knowledge%2C%20disruption%20in%20services%20and%20increased%20recruitment%20costs%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Axis%20Bank%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axisbank.com%2Fmedia-centre%2Fboard-of-directors%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eboard%20of%20directors%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20which%20at%20present%20includes%20a%20former%20RBI%20deputy%20governor%20(to%20be%20appointed%20as%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fbanking%2Ffinance%2Fbanking%2Faxis-bank-names-n-s-vishwanathan-as-part-time-non-executive-chairman%2Farticleshow%2F101050016.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Echairman%20of%20the%20board%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20October%2027%2C%202023)%20and%20an%20ex-RBI%20executive%20director%2C%20needs%20to%20devote%20more%20efforts%20to%20addressing%20the%20phenomenon%20of%20rising%20attrition.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20directors%20also%20need%20to%20be%20more%20transparent%20in%20educating%20stakeholders%20on%20why%20the%20current%20measures%20have%20proved%20inadequate%2C%20and%20what%20further%20specific%20measures%20are%20being%20considered%20to%20address%20the%20issue.%20The%20apathy%20of%20the%2013-member%20FY2023%20board%20with%20regard%20to%20attrition%20is%20particularly%20surprising%2C%20as%20eight%20of%20the%20directors%20(an%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20the%20board)%20declared%20a%20specialisation%20in%20human%20resources%20management%20(p.%20141-142%20FY2023%20annual%20report).%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20factor%20that%20needs%20exploration%20is%20whether%20the%20measures%20on%20which%20the%20Axis%20management%20relies%20%E2%80%93%20surveys%2C%20bots%2C%20counselling%20%E2%80%93%20provide%20employees%20a%20channel%20of%20communication%20and%20representation%20of%20their%20grievances.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETraditionally%2C%20trade%20unions%20used%20to%20provide%20such%20a%20channel%2C%20and%20they%20were%20institutionalised%20in%20the%20public%20sector%20banks.%20While%20there%20may%20have%20been%20some%20negative%20features%20to%20trade%20unionism%2C%20the%20private%20sector%20banks%20may%20have%20thrown%20the%20baby%20out%20with%20the%20bathwater%20by%20effectively%20banning%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20absence%20of%20employee%20representation%2C%20the%20only%20way%20employees%20can%20express%20their%20grievances%20is%20by%20voting%20with%20their%20feet.%20This%20problem%20afflicts%20all%20the%20private%20sector%20banks%2C%20even%20if%20Axis%20Bank%20seems%20to%20be%20the%20champion%20in%20this%20category.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20461px)%2085vw%2C%20461px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F09160507%2Funnamed-5.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22461%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F09160507%2Funnamed-5.png%20461w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F09160507%2Funnamed-5-300x183.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-662394%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22281%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENote%3A%20Select%20banks%20voluntarily%20disclosed%20attrition%20in%20FY2022%3Cbr%3ESource%3A%20Banks%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20apparent%20lack%20of%20attention%20by%20the%20Axis%20Bank%20board%20to%20attrition%20has%20ominous%20implications%3B%20either%20they%20are%20aware%2C%20but%20despite%20RBI%20concerns%2C%20they%20are%20relatively%20unworried%3B%20or%20they%20are%20fully%20aware%2C%20but%20are%20deliberately%20withholding%20public%20discussion%20to%20avoid%20censure%20and%20negative%20publicity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPresent%20Axis%20Bank%20board%20of%20directors%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F09160649%2Funnamed-6.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F09160649%2Funnamed-6.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F09160649%2Funnamed-6-300x115.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F09160649%2Funnamed-6-1024x392.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-662395%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22459%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Axis%20Bank%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESadly%2C%20in%20the%20recent%20past%2C%20this%20analyst%20has%20had%20to%20document%20major%20contradictions%20between%20Axis%20Bank%E2%80%99s%20public%20commentary%20and%20the%20facts%20in%20the%20public%20domain.%20In%20its%20FY2022%20and%20FY2023%20annual%20reports%2C%20the%20Bank%20commented%20on%20how%20it%20aspires%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cnumber%201%E2%80%9D%20in%20customer%20satisfaction%2C%20while%20withholding%20the%20information%20to%20stakeholders%20that%20Axis%20Bank%20was%20the%20private%20sector%20market%20leader%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhemindrahazari.com%2F2023%2F06%2F20%2Fwill-citis-retail-customers-stick-with-axis-bank-the-private-sector-market-leader-in-customer-complaints%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ecustomer%20complaints%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20FY2022%20(latest%20industry%20data).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20the%20bank%20publicly%20claims%20it%20has%20impressive%20tools%20to%20monitor%20employee%20wellbeing%2C%20such%20as%20repeated%20HR%20surveys%2C%20AI%20bots%20to%20engage%20in%20HR%20conversations%20and%20professional%20counsellors%20to%20alleviate%20stress%2C%20finding%20out%20the%20causes%20for%20rising%20attrition%20should%20not%20be%20difficult.%20As%20rising%20attrition%20results%20in%20disruption%2C%20customer%20dissatisfaction%20and%20higher%20staff%20costs%20of%20hiring%20and%20training%2C%20the%20causes%20should%20be%20disclosed.%20At%20the%20bank%E2%80%99s%20annual%20general%20meeting%20scheduled%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axisbank.com%2Fdocs%2Fdefault-source%2Fannual-general-meeting%2F29th-annual-general-meeting%2Fnotice-convening-the-29th-annual-general-meeting.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EJuly%2028%2C%202023%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20shareholders%20must%20demand%20an%20explanation%20from%20the%20board%20of%20directors.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20as%20Axis%20Bank%20keeps%20reaffirming%20openness%20in%20its%20FY2023%20annual%20report%2C%20when%20this%20analyst%20specifically%20sent%20queries%20to%20the%20bank%20on%20customer%20complaints%20and%20attrition%2C%20the%20bank%20declined%20to%20respond.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20bank%20publicly%20claims%20to%20welcome%20one%20and%20all%2C%20cust