0the%20cooling%20effect.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Peltier%20effect%20is%20a%20phenomenon%20in%20which%20heat%20is%20given%20out%20or%20absorbed%20when%20an%20electric%20current%20passes%20across%20a%20junction%20between%20two%20materials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBesides%2C%20on%20average%2C%20a%20single%20cooler%20requires%203%2C000%20litres%20of%20water%20per%20month%2C%20but%20our%20device%20requires%20only%20300%20ml%20of%20water.%20Thus%2C%20it%20could%20help%20save%20gallons%20of%20water%20consumed%20by%20traditional%20coolers%20and%20reduce%20the%20negative%20environmental%20impact%20of%20refrigerants%20used%20in%20air%20conditioners.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20students%20are%20also%20working%20towards%20reducing%20their%20dependency%20on%20power%20and%20using%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F294472%2Fair-conditioner-ac-works-on-solar-panel-energy-reduce-electricity-bill%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolar%20panels%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20meet%20the%20power%20requirements%20in%20a%20self-sufficient%20way%2C%20thereby%20reducing%20the%20overall%20carbon%20footprint.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHighlighting%20the%20challenges%20in%20developing%20the%20device%2C%20Sahil%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20needed%20to%20find%20out%20a%20certain%20pattern%20to%20arrange%20our%20components.%20Before%20coming%20to%20the%20final%20version%2C%20we%20tried%20multiple%20arrangements%20of%20our%20components%2C%20but%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20did%20not%20work%20as%20it%20was%20taking%20time%20to%20reduce%20the%20temperature.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCtLbE37LZj4%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCtLbE37LZj4%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_cam